    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Techniques used to create images that display a higher luminous dynamic range than is possible with a single conventional exposure. This may be achieved with a series of conventional exposures captured with differing values, or via a laser scanner with high dynamic range (HDR) texture compression that records a range in excess of what normal digital imaging techniques allow.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
